Class CustomerFile

public class CustomerFile
extends java.lang.Object

This class creates the CustomerFile objects which will store the customer information for each respective customer. There are "get" and "set" methods to initialise values to each respective instance variable and the constructor will initialise these values

this is the constructor, it will initialise values to the instance variables that create the customer record. It does not return anything so it is void but it will output a String ensuring the user that a record has been created and a copy the information with method displayAllDetails

Parameters:
fName - this is the forename string which will be assigned to forename
sName - this is the surname string which will be assigned to surname
pNum - this is the phone number which will be assigned to phoneNumber
eAddress - this is the email address which will be assigned to eAddress
hAddress - this is the home address which will be assigned to homeAddress
pCode - this is the post code which will be assigned to postCode
